{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund Psychiatric Liaison Practitioners in all GP surgeries",
        "additional_details": "GPs manage the mental health support for many patients, but often lack the specialist training. In our view, the lack of specialist input can lead to:\r\n\u2022 Patients left on doses that are too high or switched between medications without adequate protocols, leading to severe withdrawal,\r\n\u2022 Side effects like \"emotional numbness\" or \"akathisia\" being mismanaged, leading to loss of quality of life and, in some cases, increased risk of suicide\r\n\u2022 Patients reaching crisis point, putting pressure on A&E",
        "background": "Fund the employment of a dedicated psychiatrist in all GP surgeries to help \r\nsupport surgery with the drafting and oversight of titration and cross-tapering plans, and providing medication reviews as needed.\r\n",
